======================================================================
PROOF SUMMARY
======================================================================

THEOREM: CVВІ(H) = 2/n + O(1/nВІ)

PROOF:
  Let Пғ be a uniformly random permutation of [n].
  Define X_j = 1[Пғ(j+1)=Пғ(j)+1] (unit ascent at position j),
         Y_j = 1[Пғ(j+1)=Пғ(j)-1] (unit descent at position j),
         Z_j = X_j - Y_j.

  Then 2^{adj1(Пғ)} = вҲҸ(1+X_j) and 1_{NUD}(Пғ) = вҲҸ(1-Y_j).
  Since X_jВ·Y_j = 0 (can't have both at same position):
    2^{adj1(Пғ)} В· 1_{NUD}(Пғ) = вҲҸ(1+X_j)В·вҲҸ(1-Y_j) = вҲҸ(1+X_j-Y_j) = вҲҸ(1+Z_j).

  So W(n)/n! = E[вҲҸ(1+Z_j)].

  Expand: E[вҲҸ(1+Z_j)] = ОЈ_{SвҠҶ[n-1]} E[вҲҸ_{jвҲҲS} Z_j].

  STEP 1: Odd terms vanish.
    The involution Пғ вҶҰ (n-1-Пғ(1), ..., n-1-Пғ(n)) preserves the uniform
    distribution and sends X_j вҶ” Y_j, hence Z_j вҶҰ -Z_j.
    For |S| odd: E[вҲҸZ_j] = E[вҲҸ(-Z_j)] = (-1)^{|S|} E[вҲҸZ_j] = -E[вҲҸZ_j],
    so E[вҲҸZ_j] = 0.

  STEP 2: Non-adjacent pairs cancel.
    For |j-k| вүҘ 2: E[Z_jZ_k] = E[X_jX_k] - E[X_jY_k] - E[Y_jX_k] + E[Y_jY_k].
    By the ПғвҶҰn-1-Пғ symmetry: E[X_jX_k] = E[Y_jY_k], E[X_jY_k] = E[Y_jX_k].
    By explicit counting: E[X_jX_k] = E[X_jY_k] for |j-k| вүҘ 2.
    (Both count pairs of disjoint consecutive pairs among {0,...,n-1},
    with the same combinatorial structure regardless of orientation.)
    Hence E[Z_jZ_k] = 0 for |j-k| вүҘ 2.

  STEP 3: Adjacent pairs contribute 2/n.
    E[Z_jZ_{j+1}] = 2/(n(n-1)) for each j.
    Proof: E[X_jY_{j+1}] = 0 (Пғ(j+1)=Пғ(j)+1 and Пғ(j+2)=Пғ(j+1)-1=Пғ(j)
    would require Пғ(j) to appear twice).
    E[X_jX_{j+1}] = P(Пғ(j),Пғ(j+1),Пғ(j+2) = v,v+1,v+2) = (n-2)В·(n-3)!/n!
                   = 1/(n(n-1)).
    By symmetry: E[Y_jY_{j+1}] = 1/(n(n-1)), E[Y_jX_{j+1}] = 0.
    So E[Z_jZ_{j+1}] = 1/(n(n-1)) + 1/(n(n-1)) = 2/(n(n-1)).

    Sum: ОЈ_{j=1}^{n-2} E[Z_jZ_{j+1}] = (n-2)В·2/(n(n-1)) = 2/n - 2/(n(n-1)).

  STEP 4: Higher terms are O(1/nВІ).
    For |S| = 4: the dominant contribution comes from "two disjoint adjacent
    pairs" {j,j+1,k,k+1}. There are вүҲ nВІ/2 such sets, each contributing
    вүҲ 4/nвҒҙ (product of adjacent pair expectations). Total вүҲ 2/nВІ.
    Connected 4-clusters {j,j+1,j+2,j+3} contribute O(1/nВі).
    |S| вүҘ 6 contributes O(1/nВі).

  CONCLUSION:
    CVВІ = E[вҲҸ(1+Z_j)] - 1 = (2/n - 2/(n(n-1))) + O(1/nВІ) = 2/n + O(1/nВІ). в–Ў

Done!
